LLM-Generated Code Notice

Portions of the code in this repo were generated by an LLM (a.k.a. "generative AI"), 
such as Claude Code, or similar. In a recent action by the US Supreme Court,
they declined to hear the case disputing the US Copyright Office denying 
copyright application on AI-generated images because the images lacked a human
creator. This implies that regardless of whether a creation could normally be 
copyrighted, if "created" by an LLM, it is not eligible for copyright protection. 

- [Copyright Office Letter of Refusal](https://web.archive.org/web/20260303164310/https://www.copyright.gov/rulings-filings/review-board/docs/a-recent-entrance-to-paradise.pdf)
- [The Verge article about the Supreme Court action](https://web.archive.org/web/20260308162549/https://www.theverge.com/policy/887678/supreme-court-ai-art-copyright)

Accordingly, it would seem that the portions of this code generated by LLMs is 
not eligible for protection and cannot meaningfully be licensed. These portions 
may be identified by commit messages that indicate the code was co-authored by 
the LLM. All other portions, written by human contributors, are covered by the 
MIT License above.
